  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Cook",
  "description": "<p><strong>About Us </strong></p><p>Chip Bee Bistro is a new casual-dining concept by High Note Hospitality Group. We’re a space for warmth, creativity, and genuine connections—built on authenticity, artistic curiosity, and old-school hospitality meets grown-up bistro life.<br /></p><p><strong>What We're Looking For</strong></p><p>You will support daily kitchen operations by preparing and cooking food items according to standard recipes, maintaining hygiene and safety standards, and collaborating with the kitchen team to ensure smooth and timely food service.<br /></p><p><strong>Role & Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Prepare and cook food items following established recipes and guidelines to ensure consistent quality</li><li>Assist with basic kitchen tasks such as heating, portioning, and assembling dishes</li><li>Support food plating and service under supervision</li><li>Clean and organize kitchen workstations, equipment, and utensils to uphold hygiene and safety</li><li>Follow food safety, hygiene, and workplace safety protocols to maintain a safe kitchen environment</li><li>Assist with proper handling, storage, and stock rotation of ingredients</li><li>Collaborate with the kitchen team during service to support timely and efficient food preparation</li></ul><p><strong>What You Bring</strong></p><ul><li>Previous kitchen or food-handling experience to contribute to kitchen efficiency</li><li>Willingness to learn and follow instructions to adapt to kitchen processes</li><li>Ability to work effectively in a fast-paced kitchen environment</li><li>Physical fitness to stand for long hours during shifts</li><li>Responsible, punctual, and able to work well within a team</li><li>Availability to work evenings, weekends, and public holidays as required</li></ul><p><strong>What We Offer</strong></p><ul><li>Salary Range: $2,000 – $2,500</li><li>5-day work week (44 hours per week)</li><li>Group medical and hospitalization coverage</li><li>Staff discounts</li><li>Meals and transport benefits</li><li>Training and career development opportunities</li><li>Discretionary year-end bonus</li></ul>",
